rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all astronauts. These are the people that are trained in a space program to command, pilot, or serve as a crew member of a spacecraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronaut

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an astronaut to a space agency with which he or she is affiliated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Space Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an astronaut to a space mission in which he or she took part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Space Missions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an astronaut to the total amount of time in minutes spent in space missions (time of launch to end of mission). Note that death during a space mission is a factor in calculating total space time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Space Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A rocket engine that consumes fuel in liquid form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bipropellant Rocket Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a bipropellant rocket engine to the pressure in bars of the combustion chamber of the rocket engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chamber Pressure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a bipropellant rocket engine to a standard descriptor for the means of powering the injection of the fuel into the combustion chamber of the rocket engine, e.g. expander cycle and pressure-fed cycle.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Cycle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a bipropellant rocket engine to the expansion ratio of the fuel used in the rocket engine. The expansion ratio is the ratio of the volume in liquid form of the fuel to the volume in gas form of the fuel at normal temperature and pressure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expansion Ratio

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a bipropellant rocket engine to the fuel used by the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a bipropellant rocket engine to the number of combustion chambers in the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Chambers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a bipropellant rocket engine to the oxidizer used by the engine. The oxidizer is the substance that is mixed with the fuel to create the rocket engine propellant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Oxidizer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a bipropellant rocket engine to the ratio of oxidizer to fuel that is required by the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Oxidizer/Fuel Ratio

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a bipropellant rocket engine to its mass in kilograms when it is fully loaded with fuel and oxidizer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wet Mass
Launch Payload
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type has no data and no properties. Typically, "payload" would be defined as an attribute. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all launch sites. This is area and facilities where rockets or spacecraft lift off within a spaceport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Pad

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a launch site to a space mission that originated at the launch site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Missions Landed Here

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a launch site to a space rocket that took off from the launch site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rockets Launched Here
Mission destination
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no need for this type. Just use astronomy.celestial_object. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:astronomy.celestial_object]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: missions_sent_here
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the types of spaceflight missions undertaken. These include types like lunar landing, Reconnaissance, ISS assembly, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mission Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rockets. A rocket is any vehicle that gains propulsion from a rocket engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the country that sponsored the manufacture and launch of the rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country Of Origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the diameter of the rocket in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the height of the rocket in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the date of the final launch of the rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Flight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to a site from which the rocket was launched.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the date of the initial launch of the rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maiden Flight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the company that manufactured the rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the mass of the rocket in kilograms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to the total number of stages, or components that are jettisoned during flight, that the rocket has.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number Of Stages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a rocket to a standard descriptor for a function of the rocket, e.g. human spaceflight, space station or international ballistic missile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Function

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a rocket to one of the stages that make up the rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket to a standard descriptor for the status of the rocket, e.g. canceled or operational.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rocket engines. These are the engines that are used as part of rockets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to the time interval during which the rocket engine was designed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Design Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its diameter in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its mass in kilograms without fuel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dry Mass
Government designation
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its height in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its specific impulse (a measure of the rocket's efficiency) at sea level in seconds per unit of weight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Isp (Sea Level)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its specific impulse (a measure of the rocket's efficiency) in a vacuum in seconds per unit of weight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Isp (Vacuum)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to the company that manufactured the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufactured by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to the person or organization that designed the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designed by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a rocket engine to a standard descriptor for the status of the development of the rocket engine, e.g. study, test fired or flown.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: it's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its thrust at sea level, viz. the amount of force required by the engine to accelerate 1 kilogram of mass at the rate of 1 meter per second squared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thrust (Sea Level)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to its thrust in a vacuum, viz. the amount of force required by the engine to accelerate 1 kilogram of mass at the rate of 1 meter per second squared.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thrust (Vacuum)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket engine to the time interval during which the rocket engine was used in rocket launches.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Use Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a rocket engine to a rocket stage in which the engine is a component.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Stages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the means of powering the injection of the fuel into the combustion chamber of a rocket engine, e.g. expander cycle and pressure-fed cycle.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Cycle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rocket engine designers. These are the people and organizations with some role in the design of rocket engines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Designer
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:event.agent instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.agent]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Fuel
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:spaceflight.rocket_fuel instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[mso:spaceflight.rocket_fuel]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rocket engine manufacturers. These are the producers of rocket engines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rocket engine oxidizers. These are the substances mixed with fuel to create rocket engine propellant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Oxidizer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the status of the development of a rocket engine, e.g. study, test fired or flown.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Engine Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of rocket fuels. This is the material used by mso:spaceflight.rocket_engine to provide a spacecraft with propulsion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Fuel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for a function of a rocket, e.g. human spaceflight, space station or international ballistic missile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Function

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking a standard descriptor for a function of a rocket, e.g. human spaceflight, space station or international ballistic missile, to a rocket that serves this function.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rockets Supporting this Function

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all spaceports. These are the large sites for launching and receiving spacecraft. These sites may have several mso:spaceflight.launch_sites as parts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Launch Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a space port to the country that has authority over it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Controlling Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a space port to the location of the spaceport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a space port to the space agency that has authority over it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Controlling Space Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all rocket manufacturers. These are the mso:business.operations that build and manufacture rockets and parts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a rocket manufacturer to a rocket that the company manufactured.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rockets Manufactured

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A section of a rocket that is jettisoned during flight in order to reduce the mass of the remaining rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Stage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket stage to the amount of time in seconds that the stage is designed to be used before it is jettisoned.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Burn Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket stage to the engine that is used in the stage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a rocket stage to the fuel that is used by the stage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a rocket stage to the number of engines included in the stage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a rocket stage to the rocket of which the stage is a component.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a rocket stage to a number indicating the order of the stage with respect to other stages of the given rocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stage Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a rocket stage to the amount of thrust in Newtons provided by the stage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thrust

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the status of a rocket, e.g. canceled or operational.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rocket Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a standard descriptor of a status, e.g. operational or cancelled, to a rocket that currently has this status.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rockets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all artificial satellites. These are the objects that have been intentionally placed into orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the mean altitude of the satellite's orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Altitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the date that the satellite first became operational.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Began Operating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the date that the satellite ceased operations. Note that a non-operational satellite may still be in orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ceased Operating
COSPAR Id

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dry Mass (kg)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.dry_mass instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.dry_mass]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the amount of time required by the satellite to pass the same point at nadir. This differs from orbit, which is the time it takes to complete a revolution.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ground repeat time
Launch Date
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use projects.project.start_date, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:projects.project.start_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Mass (kg)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.launch_mass instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.launch_mass]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the site on earth from which the satellite was launched.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a satellite to the rocket that was used to launch the satellite into orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Vehicle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a satellite to the number used by the North American Aerospace Defense Command to identify the satellite.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a satellite to a standard descriptor for the kind of orbit that the satellite is in.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a satellite to the object that the satellite is in orbit around.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbiting
Power (watts)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.end_of_life_power instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:spaceflight.spacecraft.end_of_life_power]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a satellite to a standard descriptor for the primary use of the satellite.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primary Use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.satellite to its revisit time. This is the time that elapses between observations of the same point on earth by the satellite.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Revisit Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The satellite's speed in its orbit.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all satellite buses. rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite Bus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all spacecraft manufacturers. These are the mso:business.operations that build and manufacture spacecraft and parts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spacecraft Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a spacecraft manufacturer to a spacecraft manufactured by the company.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spacecraft Manufactured

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the distance in kilometers at which the satellite is most distant from the earth.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the angle at which the orbital plane of the satellite cuts the equatorial plane of the earth.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the distance in kilometers at which the satellite is closest to the earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Perigee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of minutes required by the satellite to orbit the earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given satellite.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of orbit of the given satellite.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship collecting data on a satellite's synchronous orbit. Synchronous orbits are those in which the satellite has a period equal to the avergae rotational period of the body being orbited and in the same direction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite Orbit, Synchronous
E / W
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longitude
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the satellite in the synchronous orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of orbit of the given satellite.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for types of satellite orbits, e.g. geostationary orbit, sun-synchronous orbit, and low earth orbit.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a space agency to an astronaut that is part of the space agency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronauts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a space agency to a spaceport over which the agency has authority.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spaceports

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of ballistic flights into or through outer space.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronauts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a space mission to a destination of the mission, e.g. the moon, Mars, ISS, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Destination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.space_mission to the total distance traveled in kilometers during the course of the mission.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a space mission to the site used to launch the spacecraft for the mission.

Space Program Sponsor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Space Programs Sponsored
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all spacecraft. These are the vehicles designed to fly in outer space, and are created for a variety of purposes, including communications, observation, navigation, and exploration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spacecraft

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its Beginning of Life mass, this is the mass in orbit at the beginning of operational life, after LEOP phase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beginning of Life Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its dimensions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dimensions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its dry mass, the mass of the spacecraft without fuel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dry Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its end of life power.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Of Life Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its identifiers like COSPAR ID and Satellite Catalog Number.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Identification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its landing mass, which includes only the mass of recovered spacecraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Landing Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its launch mass, the mass of the craft with fuel at launch time. This measurement does not include the rocket or upper stage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launch Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a spacecraft to the company that manufactured the spacecraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its orbital relationship that collects the orbital data for the craft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbital Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to the mso:spaceflight.satellite_bus that provided the basic infrastructure of the craft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite Bus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:spaceflight.spacecraft to its type, the class of spacecraft it is.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spacecraft Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the types of mso:spaceflight.spacecrafts. These are the collections of spacecrafts like GPS Block IIF and Yantar-4K2M.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spacecraft Type
